text.__SUMMARY__:
Shorea seminis is a species of plant in the Dipterocarpaceae family. It is found in Borneo Island, particularly in Sarawak, Malaysia, and the Philippines's Mindanao Island.
Diptoindonesin A is a C-glucoside of ε-viniferin isolated from S. seminis.
text.References: Ashton, P. 1998.  Shorea seminis.   2006 IUCN Red List of Threatened Species.   Downloaded on 23 August 2007.
